The 2018/2019 champion of the Nigeria Professional Football League, Enyimba Int’l Football Club, are reportedly set to unveil former Remo Stars gaffer, Fatai Osho, as the new Chief Coach next week.

Coach  Osho confirmed to National Daily that he will be unveiled and introduce to the players on Tuesday July 23, as chief coach by Enyimba boss, Chief Felix Anyansi.

The former Kogi United and Crown FC tiki-taka tactician contract terms according to a reliable source as been agreed upon and he is expected to sign his contract papers at the team’s office, on Tuesday morning.

Osho, we gathered will start work immediately as assistant to Usman Abdallah.


			
